sources.description:
Stars: Tim McCoy,  Kathleen Elliott, Frank LaRue
Director: Alan James

Saddle up for an action-packed adventure with Tim McCoy, one of the silver screen‚Äôs most iconic cowboys, in West of Rainbow's End (1938)! This classic cowboy western delivers everything fans love about the golden era of B-movie westerns: fast-paced shootouts, rugged heroes, daring rescues, and timeless tales of good versus evil.

Set against the sweeping landscapes of the Old West, in this 1938 gem, a former railroad detective (Tim McCoy) comes out of retirement to track down the killers of his foster father, Lightnin' Ed, who had been investigating a series of train robberies. Featuring thrilling horseback chases, tense standoffs, and Frank LaRue, this film embodies the charm and grit of vintage Western cinema.

Perfect for fans of classic westerns, cowboy movies, and the golden age of Hollywood, West of Rainbow's End is a must-watch for anyone who enjoys the nostalgia of early sound films. Whether you're a longtime admirer of Tim McCoy or a newcomer exploring the frontier of 1930s Westerns, this movie is a treasure.

Discover why timeless cowboy classics like this continue to captivate audiences and keep the spirit of the Old West alive. Subscribe to PizzaFLIX for more legendary films and cinematic history!

metadata.Plot: Tim arrives looking for the killer of his friend Lightning Ed. Johnson is behind the murder as he wants to buy the Carter ranch cheap so he can sell it to the railroad at a big profit. When Tim steps in to take over for Lightning Ed, Johnson and his gang make plans to finish him off.
metadata.Writer: Robert Emmett Tansey, Stanley Roberts, Gennaro Rea
metadata.Actors: Tim McCoy, Kathleen Eliot, Walter McGrail
